law.text: Any person who is a licensed landscape architect in the United States or another country where the qualifications prescribed at the time of licensing were, in the opinion of the board, equal to those prescribed in the Commonwealth at the date of application, may be granted a license.
law.history: Amended 2014 Ky. Acts ch. 90, sec. 4, effective July 15, 2014. -- Amended 1990 Ky. Acts ch. 146, sec. 2, effective July 13, 1990. -- Created 1972 Ky. Acts ch. 287, sec. 5.
